tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE land_use_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  location TEXT,
  land_type TEXT,
  land_area FLOAT,
  development_status TEXT,
  year INT
)

CREATE TABLE development_plans (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    plan_name VARCHAR(255),
    region VARCHAR(255),
    proposed_land_use VARCHAR(255),
    budget DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE historical_land_use_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    land_use_category VARCHAR(255),
    area_in_acres DECIMAL,
    year_recorded INT
)

CREATE TABLE urban_development_projects (
    project_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    project_name VARCHAR(255),
    start_date DATE,
    completion_date DATE,
    development_cost DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE trend_analysis (
    trend_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    trend_description TEXT,
    analysis_date DATE,
    analyst_name VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE DevelopmentProjects (
  project_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  project_name VARCHAR(255),
  developer VARCHAR(255),
  project_start_date DATE,
  project_end_date DATE,
  land_use_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (land_use_id) REFERENCES LandUseData(id)
);

CREATE TABLE UrbanDevelopmentPlan (
  plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  plan_name VARCHAR(255),
  plan_description TEXT,
  start_date DATE,
  end_date DATE,
  budget FLOAT
);
CREATE TABLE LandUseData (     id UUID PRIMARY KEY,     year INT,     land_type VARCHAR,     land_area FLOAT     );
CREATE TABLE UrbanDevelopment (     id UUID PRIMARY KEY,     year INT,     construction_type VARCHAR,     building_size FLOAT     );
CREATE TABLE PopulationData (     id UUID PRIMARY KEY,     year INT,     population_count INT,     city_name VARCHAR     );
CREATE TABLE EconomicIndicators (     id UUID PRIMARY KEY,     year INT,     gdp FLOAT,     unemployment_rate FLOAT     );
CREATE TABLE DevelopmentProjects (     id UUID PRIMARY KEY,     project_name VARCHAR,     start_year INT,     completion_year INT     );
